Regression Discontinuity: Figure with Points

# Install and load packages ---------------
packages <- c(
  "tidyverse",
  "haven",
  "rdd",
  "splines"
)

# Change to install = TRUE to install the required packages
pacman::p_load(packages, character.only = TRUE, install = FALSE)

# Load an example dataset ---------------
# https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/handle/10986/25030
data <- read_dta("https://github.com/worldbank/r-econ-visual-library/raw/master/Library/Data/evaluation.dta")

# Printing the first five rows of the data to visualize its structure before data wrangling
head(data)

# Data wrangling ---------------

# Set the cutoff level
cutoff <- 58

data <- data %>%
  filter(treatment_locality == 1) %>%
  mutate(treatment = (poverty_index <= cutoff))

# Printing the first five rows of the data to visualize its structure after data wrangling
head(data)
## # A tibble: 6 x 23
##   locality_identi household_ident treatment_local promotion_local eligible
##              <dbl>            <dbl>            <dbl>            <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1               26                5                1                1        1
## 2               26                5                1                1        1
## 3               26               11                1                1        1
## 4               26               11                1                1        1
## 5               26               13                1                1        1
## 6               26               13                1                1        1
## #  with 18 more variables: enrolled <dbl>, enrolled_rp <dbl>,
## #   poverty_index <dbl>, round <dbl>, health_expenditures <dbl>, age_hh <dbl>,
## #   age_sp <dbl>, educ_hh <dbl>, educ_sp <dbl>, female_hh <dbl>,
## #   indigenous <dbl>, hhsize <dbl>, dirtfloor <dbl>, bathroom <dbl>,
## #   land <dbl>, hospital_distance <dbl>, hospital <dbl>, treatment <lgl>
# Create a graph ---------------

ggplot(data, aes(x = poverty_index, y = health_expenditures, color = treatment)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.2, size = 0.1) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm, formula = y ~ bs(x, 3), size = 1.0, se = FALSE) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = cutoff, linetype = "longdash") +
  ylim(c(0, 45)) +
  labs(
    x = "Baseline Poverty Index",
    y = "Health Expenditures ($)"
  ) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set2", labels = c("Not eligible", "Eligible")) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 14),
    legend.title = element_blank(),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 11)
    )
